{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>The Hook:<\/strong> Automation isn&#8217;t just about moving data from Point A to Point B; it\u2019s about what happens in the middle.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Data Transformation via Regex<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Raw data is messy. Using a Function node or a specialized Regex node in <strong>n8n<\/strong> allows you to sanitize content before it ever hits your database.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Use Case:<\/strong> Automatically stripping out unwanted HTML tags from a WordPress excerpt or formatting currency strings for a dashboard.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Error Handling as a Feature<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A &#8220;Pro&#8221; workflow doesn&#8217;t just work when things are right\u2014it survives when things go wrong. Implementing &#8220;Error Trigger&#8221; nodes ensures that if an API call fails, you get a notification on Slack or Discord immediately, rather than finding out three days later that your site is empty.<\/p>\n","protected":false}

